[4] Brazil (Parana)
Date: Tue 29 Sep 2009
Source: O Diario do Norte do Parana [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.odiariomaringa.com.br/noticia/226745>


The Secretariat of Health of Parana warns of increasing cases of
dengue in the state during the rainy season. According to the
secretariat, Parana, must redouble its attention to the disease,
because a survey showed that 3 different serotypes of [dengue] virus
are circulating the state, which raises the possibility of an epidemic
of DHF.

Up to the end of August [2009], there were 814 confirmed cases of
dengue in Parana's municipal districts. Of these, 702 were locally
acquired -- contracted in the state itself -- and 112 were imported.
During the same period in 2008, 752 locally acquired cases were
confirmed.

Dengue preventive actions are directed to the elimination of breeding
sites of the mosquito that transmits the disease [virus], _Aedes
aegypti_, which breeds in stagnant water. Among the recommendations to
prevent the spread of the mosquito, are capping water tanks, keeping
the yard clean and [filling] plant pots with sand to prevent [this
mosquito] from reproducing.

