[6] Honduras
Date: Tue 29 Sep 2009
Source: El Heraldo (Honduras) [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.elheraldo.hn/index.php/Ediciones/2009/09/29/Noticias/Nuevo-brote-de-dengue-ataca-hondurenos>


The director of the Teaching Hospital, Juan Ramon Barahona, referred
this morning [29 Sep 2009] to a national dengue outbreak resulting
from the winter [rainy] season. The director indicated that up to now
the Teaching Hospital is treating the cases in the preventative area
and during 3 days of intensive work, 2 adults ill with dengue and 8
cases admitted in pediatrics have been reported.

Barahona, recommended that the Honduras population comply with the
appropriate measures to prevent this epidemic that puts the population
at risk. Similarly, he called for people who live in outlying areas
from the city to bury their trash to avoid attracting all types of
insects.

"This new dengue pathology has increased severely, which has us a bit
worried and why we ask the people to comply with the hygiene measures
that are being reported in the media," said the Director. The doctor
indicated the extermination of these insect [mosquito] vectors which
cause [transmit] dengue [virus] must proceed urgently.

